filters: Only vehicles in test.csv need predictions
All rows in test.csv must have Mileage predictions
sub_questions: How does vehicle age affect mileage?
How do different brands/models have different mileage patterns?
How does new vs used status affect mileage?
What features (MPG, Engine, etc.) correlate with mileage?
How to handle missing values in training data?

schema_conflicts: Car_Rates.csv has rating columns not in other files

scale_issues: MPG column contains range strings (e.g., '26–33') not numeric values
Mileage has very wide range (0 to 147179+)
money values vary widely by vehicle type
cross_source_conflicts: Car_Rates.csv has many missing values (empty cells)
New_York_cars.csv has inconsistent formatting in feature columns (spaces, lists)
test.csv has certification types (e.g., 'Ford Certified') not in training

format_notes: Car_Rates.csv has inconsistent spacing in Car_name column
New_York_cars.csv feature columns contain pipe-separated lists within cells
MPG column uses en dash (–) instead of hyphen

constraints: New vehicles typically have low mileage (<100)
MPG ranges must be valid positive numbers
Mileage predictions must be written to result.csv
derived_filters: Consider separate models for new vs used vehicles
Filter out extreme outliers in Mileage (>300,000)
statistical_tests: Regression of Mileage on vehicle features
output_format_requirements: result.csv must have same row count as test.csv
